# ERP Dropdown / Overlay Z-Index Standard

**Version:** V1  
**Phase:** ERP GLOBAL UI.4G+ (enforced from DMS.4 closure, 2026-06-14)  
**Status:** ACTIVE  

---

## Canonical Z-Index Stack

This is the **single source of truth** for all overlay z-index values in the ERP app.
Do NOT use `z-50` for any portal-rendered overlay. Do NOT deviate from this stack.

| Layer | Z-index | File / Component |
|---|---|---|
| App content | base (auto) | — |
| Workspace tab bar | `z-[30]` | `workspace-tab-bar.tsx` |
| ERPDrawerForm / Sheet | `z-[50]` | `sheet.tsx` (base) |
| ERPChildDialogForm overlay | `z-[100]` | `erp-child-dialog-form.tsx` (overlay) |
| ERPChildDialogForm content | `z-[110]` | `erp-child-dialog-form.tsx` (content) |
| **Select / Popover / DropdownMenu** | **`z-[120]`** | `select.tsx`, `popover.tsx`, `dropdown-menu.tsx` |
| **ERPCombobox PopoverContent** | **`z-[120]`** | `erp-combobox.tsx` |
| **AlertDialog / confirmation dialog** | **`z-[130]`** | `alert-dialog.tsx` |
| **Tooltip** | **`z-[140]`** | `tooltip.tsx` |
| Toast / Sonner | `z-[9999]` | sonner |

---

## Rules

### 1. Never use `z-50` for portal-rendered components

`z-50` was the shadcn/Radix default. This ERP project raised all portaled overlay defaults.
After the ERP GLOBAL UI.4G fix, **`z-50` is reserved only for non-portaled positioned elements**.

❌ **Wrong** — will render behind child dialogs:
```tsx
<SelectContent className="z-50 ...">
```

✅ **Correct** — always use `z-[120]` (already the default in `select.tsx`):
```tsx
<SelectContent>  {/* default z-[120] is correct */}
```

### 2. All Select/Popover/DropdownMenu are globally at `z-[120]`

The following UI primitives have their defaults set to `z-[120]`:
- `src/components/ui/select.tsx` → `SelectContent` (Positioner + Popup)
- `src/components/ui/popover.tsx` → `PopoverContent`
- `src/components/ui/dropdown-menu.tsx` → `DropdownMenuContent` (Positioner + Popup)

Do **NOT** override these to a lower value (`z-50`, `z-10`, etc.) inside forms or dialogs.
Do **NOT** add a `className` that overrides `z-[120]` downward.

### 3. ERPCombobox inside ERPChildDialogForm is the approved async picker

For any field sourced from the database (categories, document types, parties, employees, etc.)
inside an `ERPChildDialogForm`, always use `ERPCombobox`, not bare `<Select>`.

`ERPCombobox` explicitly sets `z-[120]` on its `PopoverContent` (redundant with the default
but intentional for documentation).

❌ **Wrong — async data in a child dialog using bare Select:**
```tsx
<ERPChildDialogForm ...>
  <Select value={form.category_id} ...>
    <SelectContent>
      {categories.map(c => <SelectItem key={c.id} value={String(c.id)}>{c.name_en}</SelectItem>)}
    </SelectContent>
  </Select>
</ERPChildDialogForm>
```

✅ **Correct — async data uses ERPCombobox:**
```tsx
<ERPChildDialogForm ...>
  <ERPCombobox
    options={categories.map(c => ({ value: c.id, label: c.name_en }))}
    value={form.category_id}
    onValueChange={(v) => setForm(f => ({ ...f, category_id: v }))}
  />
</ERPChildDialogForm>
```

### 4. AlertDialog must appear above dropdowns

`AlertDialog` (confirm/destroy dialogs) are at `z-[130]`. This is correct and already set in
`alert-dialog.tsx`. Never lower the AlertDialog overlay or content below `z-[130]`.

### 5. Tooltip must appear above all overlays

Tooltips are at `z-[140]`. This is already set in `tooltip.tsx`.
Never add a tooltip inside an AlertDialog (it would render behind at `z-[130]`).
If needed inside a dialog, pass the tooltip `className="z-[150]"`.

### 6. ERPChildDialogForm z-index must not change without team approval

`ERPChildDialogForm` uses `z-[100]` (overlay) and `z-[110]` (content).
Changing these values breaks the entire overlay stacking contract.
Always update ALL related z-index values together if the base ever needs to change.

### 7. Do NOT add `isolate` to form containers or section panels

The CSS `isolation: isolate` (Tailwind class `isolate`) creates a new stacking context.
If added to a container that wraps a portal trigger, it can trap z-index values.
Only use `isolate` on overlay elements themselves (e.g., the dialog positioner).

---

## How This Was Discovered

After ERP GLOBAL UI.4G raised `ERPChildDialogForm` to `z-[100]`/`z-[110]`, the
`SelectContent`, `PopoverContent`, and `DropdownMenuContent` were left at Tailwind's default
`z-50`. This caused Select dropdowns inside DMS admin child dialogs to render **behind** the
dialog panel — appearing invisible to users.

Fix applied 2026-06-14 (ERP DMS.4 closure):
- `select.tsx` Positioner + Popup: `z-50` → `z-[120]`
- `dropdown-menu.tsx` Positioner + Popup: `z-50` → `z-[120]`
- `popover.tsx` Content: `z-50` → `z-[120]`
- `alert-dialog.tsx` Overlay + Content: `z-50` → `z-[130]`
- `tooltip.tsx` Positioner + Popup + Arrow: `z-50` → `z-[140]`

---

## When Adding New Overlay Components

If you add a **new UI primitive** that renders in a portal (e.g., a date picker, color picker,
command palette, context menu), assign its z-index based on this stack:

- Floating picker / command palette: `z-[120]`
- Modal dialog: `z-[110]`
- Confirmation / destructive modal: `z-[130]`
- Tooltip / hint: `z-[140]`

Never use `z-50` for portaled components. Update this rule file when adding new layers.
